4:
Ladies and gentlemen, you are in luck! 
It's time for the show to begin!
5:
Give it up for our undefeated arena 
beauty! The one, the only...
11:
Thanks for coming, everyone! Let's 
make this next bout a match for the 
ages! Now, what would a dance be, 
without a partner?
14:
Calm as ever, I see! But just wait 'til she 
gets a look at the hulking horror 
behind that gate, folks!
16:
If I were you, I wouldn't blink!
Let the shoooow—
30: How did you find the match, Alk?
34:
It was amazing! The swordplay was 
nuts—I've never seen someone dance 
so elegantly with a blade!
38:
I'm happy you enjoyed yourself. It's 
a relief knowing my bodyguard 
appreciates good technique.
41:
I get the feeling that, with skills like 
yours, you don't really need 
protection...
43:
We mostly need you to protect Eclair 
from herself—someone needs to 
ensure she rests on her days off.
45: I need to watch... Eclair herself?
47:
Indeed. She spoils her fans far too 
much. You need to keep them away 
from each other.
48:
Why, just last week Eclair spent her 
ENTIRE day off signing autographs!
50:
It's no trouble—Signing a few photos is 
much easier than fighting.
53:
Be that as it may, you need rest if 
you're going to remain competitive!
55:
See what you're dealing with, Alk? Even 
if you're not likely to walk into any sort 
of danger, you keep a careful eye on 
her.
56:
Now then, have a restful holiday! And 
I do mean restful!
62:
It never gets boring, at least! Now, 
come on! We've got places to be.
66:
Huh? You just fought? Shouldn't you 
take a break today?
69:
As if. I almost never get a day off. 
I have to get out there and feed my 
soul, don't I!
73:
It hungers for adventure! It thirsts for 
fun! That's why we have to make the 
most of today!
79:
This place looks nice for a break. Shall 
we do lunch here?
82:
A mountainside picnic is nice and all, 
but...
Well, it's not the most exciting, is it?
Are you sure you wouldn't rather be in 
town?
84:
Nah, I don't want to cause a ruckus in 
the city.
87:
Besides, I had plenty of fun filling the 
picnic basket with you. I hear you're 
a killer cook—I've been excited for 
lunch all day!
89:
It's our special time together. And 
I wouldn't have it any other way!
93:
I wasn't expecting you to enjoy the 
simple things in life.
97:
Yeah, people misread me all the time. 
Every day I participate in all these 
intense events; it makes you 
appreciate a little normalcy.
100:
Of course, being a potato is a great 
way to rest your body. But it's also 
depressing. The mind needs 
stimulation too, you know?
103:
It's moments like today that really heal 
the soul. Small, unassuming moments 
that bring us together. Thanks for 
humoring me, Alk.
109:
Actually, I think I know the perfect 
place for you. Want to check it out?
113:
This is a beautiful place. Quiet, calm, 
and warm...
116:
You can come whenever you'd like. 
You can even join us on our 
adventures—when you have free time, 
of course!
121:
Hah, you drive a hard bargain. 
But I can manage that.
125:
And for my part, whenever YOU have 
some free time, you can come to the 
arena and see my bouts whenever 
you'd like. Special seats are on the 
house.
133:
I think we can work with those terms! 
Welcome to the team, Eclair!
